C86/OS

A minimalistic 32-bit operating system written entirely in x86 assembly.

FEATURES

- Protected Mode (32-bit)
- Preemptive multitasking (round-robin scheduler)
- Text mode 80x50 (VGA)
- Virtual File System (ramdisk)
- Memory manager (kmalloc/kfree)
- Custom shell

DRIVERS

- PS/2 Keyboard
- PATA/IDE (read only)
- PCI bus scanner
- RTC (Real-Time Clock)
- PC Speaker
- Serial port (COM1)
- RTL8139 (detection only)

SHELL COMMANDS

help      - Show available commands
ls        - List files
cat FILE  - Display file contents
ps        - List running processes
meminfo   - Show memory usage
cpuinfo   - Display CPU information
uname     - Show kernel version
osfetch   - Display system info with ASCII art
calc      - Simple calculator
whoami    - Show current user
date      - Display current date and time
echo      - Print text to screen
echo -com - Send text to COM1 port
pci       - List PCI devices
pata      - Detect PATA drives
pata_size - Show disk size
pata_chs  - Show CHS parameters
beep      - Test PC speaker
clear     - Clear screen
reboot    - Reboot system

BUILDING

Requirements: FASM (Flat Assembler)

fasm bootloader.asm bootloader.bin
fasm kernel.asm kernel.bin

CREATE BOOTABLE IMAGE

dd if=/dev/zero of=floppy.img bs=512 count=2880
dd if=bootloader.bin of=floppy.img conv=notrunc
dd if=kernel.bin of=floppy.img bs=512 seek=1 conv=notrunc

RUN

qemu-system-i386 -fda floppy.img -vga std

